model.implementations.components.manifests

Class CompoundManifest

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.implementations.components.manifests.BasicManifest
      • model.implementations.components.manifests.SignedManifest
        • model.implementations.components.manifests.CompoundManifest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Manifest

    public class CompoundManifest
extends SignedManifest
    A compound is an immutable collection of (references to) atoms or other compounds (contents). Compounds do not contain data - they refer to data - and are identified by GUID (derived from their contents).

    Intuition:
    Compounds are provided to permit related atoms and compounds to be gathered together (think of folders, zip files, packages etc. without containment).

    A compound can be used for de-duplication. Two collections of data (atoms and compounds) might contain the same content. The data does not have to be duplicated for each compound, since we can uniquely refer to the data from the compound itself.
    Manifest describing a Compound.

    Manifest - GUID
    ManifestType - COMPOUND
    Signature - signature of the manifest
    Contents - contents of this compound

    Author:
    Simone I. Conte "sic2@st-andrews.ac.uk"
